-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Program description.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 TxtColor is a little program which syntax highlight a simple text file
 (which can be a C, C++, or other language source code) and output the result
 in a html file.

 syntax:
    txtcolor text_file_to_convert.ext text_file_out.html (tab_size)
    
 supported file types:
    c, cxx, cc, cpp, h, hpp => C/C++ source files
	other => simple text files

 notes:
  - The file type is detected with the filename extension.
  - tab_size is the number of space to insert when a tab char is encoutered.
    -> 1 by default.
    
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 How make the program ?
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
 Just make an executable from the C source file txtcolor.c with a ANSI C
 compiler (GCC, Visual C++, ...).

